{
  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "The dispatch table for The AI GTM Engineer router (skill.md). Data, not prose. Each entry maps a buyer phrase to a target, prefixed with its mode (ENTRY | LEARN | DIAGNOSE | BUILD | OPERATE | SCALE) and the path or behavior the router routes to. The router reads the mode prefix to pick the lane and the path to load the right file. Validated against the built tree 2026-07-01: every module, calculator, academy file, routine, and scale.md target resolves to a real file.",
    "target_format": "<MODE> <path-or-behavior>",
    "kinds": {
      "kickoff": "canonical or legacy 'Start my ... engagement.' phrase; resolves forever (legacy-phrase regression suite)",
      "install": "install/claim command the buyer pastes; lands in the ENTRY shell",
      "trigger": "natural-language intent that routes straight to a mode target, skipping the three-door fork",
      "learn": "LEARN-mode education request",
      "operate": "OPERATE-mode routine/portfolio request",
      "scale": "SCALE-mode growth/next-system request"
    },
    "fallback": "A GTM-shaped request that matches no entry and no negative gets the three-door clarifier (Teach / Diagnose / Build), never a guess. See skill.md, the three-door fallback.",
    "negatives_note": "Too vague to route confidently. Do NOT guess a module. Open the three-door clarifier and let the buyer's next answer route.",
    "routing_precedence": "A teach / explain / how-does-X-work prefix always wins over a bare-system BUILD trigger: 'teach me ICP' routes LEARN academy/primers/icp, not BUILD modules/icp. Match learn-kind phrases before bare-system triggers so a teaching request never lands in a paid BUILD gate.",
    "entry_kickoff_note": "A kickoff whose target is the ENTRY shell does NOT skip the three-door fork; its mode IS the first-session script, which opens with the doors. Only non-ENTRY kickoff and trigger phrases skip the fork (skill.md routing rule 1)."
  },
